ratings.comment: I think she was getting our class and previous classes mixed up. When we went over poorly tested Exam questions, she would say that she had said it in class but she did not! I would know because I write everything down and record lectures. She complains and tells us about her health issues everyday. :) I will say she is helpful outside of class.

Sue does not like to admit she is wrong. One day she started lecturing on the next week's material and blamed it on the other professor. She is not available outside of class. She does not get along with her co-professor, and it can be uncomfortable. I appreciated the pediatric information she threw into her lectures.

Sue was seriously such a sweet woman. She was very straight to the point and got stuff done without wasting time. This class is very easy to get an A in as long as you go to discussion and follow the directions on the three big assignments (that are very easy). She definitely cares about students and was very nice and engaging during discussion.

Sue was awesome! Works well with students and genuinely cares. She doesn't waste time and makes it very clear what she expects as far as participationgrading. An AAB is definitely obtainable as long as you don't miss a discussion worth too many points (extra credit offered can help balance out the loss of maybe 1).
